A Simple Test of Rex
====================

Rex generates scanners for several compilers:

test   | language | compiler               | code
---------------------------------------------------
C      | C        | cc                     | ASCII
C++    | C++      | g++, egcs              | ASCII
MC     | Modula 2 | MOCKA (mc)             | ASCII
M2C    | Modula 2 | SUN Modula (m2c)       | ASCII
Ada    | Ada      | GNU Ada gnat (gcc)     | ASCII
Eiffel | Eiffel 3 | SIG Eiffel/S 1.3 (ecc) | ASCII
Java   | Java     | SUN javac              | ASCII
CS     | C        | cc                     | EBCDIC
MS     | Modula   | MOCKA (mc)             | EBCDIC

To run a test use:

   make <test> MLIB=...

where MLIB (=reuse) is the directory containing the Modula library.
